entries.title_d: Occasionally an Imperial ship will enter the Dathomir system. These ships are to be captured and the pilots turned over to the Inquistion for questioning.
entries.title: Dathomir System: Capture the Rogue Imperial Vessels Duty
entries.thanks_5: Oh good, you save me. Now how about you let me go.
entries.thanks_4: Should have let them destroy me.
entries.thanks_3: Hmmm, I think I would have rather had the rebels blow me up.
entries.thanks_2: Oh good, you save me. Now how about you let me go.
entries.thanks_1: Should have let them destroy me.
entries.taunt_5: Ha! I laugh at your pathetic attempts to defeat me.
entries.taunt_4: You are not very good, are you.
entries.taunt_3: You may take my life but you can never take my freedom!
entries.taunt_2: Beg! Maybe I will let you live.
entries.target_disabled: The engines are out on the ship. Start your docking procedure.
entries.recovery_success: Alright we have the trespasser. Nice work, pilot.
entries.quest_recover_d: Once disabled, move in close to the target vessel and wait for the capture process to begin.
entries.quest_location_d: A navigation waypoint to an unauthorized vessel will be given to you once you enter the Dathomir system.
entries.quest_escort_d: Follow the vessel back to a safe jump location. Make sure they arrive alive since any one of them could be a Rebel spy.
entries.quest_disable_d: Intercept and disable these unauthorized vessels before they can leave the system.
entries.panic_5: Just let them destroy me. Better that then the Inquisition.
entries.panic_4: Just let them destroy me. Better that then the Inquisition.
entries.panic_3: Great, first I get caught and now this...just isn't my day.
entries.panic_2: Just let them destroy me. Better that then the Inquisition.
entries.panic_1: Great, first I get caught and now this...just isn't my day.
entries.failed_escape: You let them get away. That is unacceptable. Return to your commander immediately.
entries.failed_destroy: You were told to bring that ship back to us in one piece. Failure is never rewarded. Speak to your superior immediately.
entries.complete_5: The rogue ship is back in Imperial hands and the Inquisition is questioning the pilot. Nice work.

entries.complete: The rogue ship is back in Imperial hands and the Inquisition is questioning the pilot. Nice work.
entries.capture_phase_2_5: I will just tell them I got lost. Do you think they will buy that?
entries.capture_phase_2_3: The Inquisition is going to have a field day with me.
entries.capture_phase_2_2: Fine. We will do whatever you want.
entries.capture_phase_2_1: Okay...okay. We will set autopilot. Just don't blow us out of space.
entries.capture_phase_2: Okay...okay. We will set autopilot. Just don't blow us out of space.
entries.capture_phase_1_5: Well at least you are not going to kill us.
entries.capture_phase_1_4: Hey, I have an idea. Let us go!
entries.capture_phase_1_3: Do you know what they are going to do to us?
entries.capture_phase_1_2: Now our commander is going to hear about this.
entries.capture_phase_1_1: Hey, how about you just let us go?
entries.capture_phase_1: Hey, how about you just let us go?
entries.capture_complete: The ship is set on autopilot and will head back to HQ.
entries.arrival_phase_2: We have a lock on their location. Capture those ships and bring them back to HQ. Any escort that they have with them are expendable.
entries.arrival_phase_1: Getting a lock on the unauthorized ships. Stand by.
entries.abort: Please don't report this. You will not see us in this region again, I swear.
